## Limitations

The findings presented in this report are based on a limited selection of sources and may not capture the full range of perspectives on this topic. Additionally, the impact of rewards on student motivation and performance can be influenced by numerous factors, including cultural context, individual student differences, and the nature of the rewards. Further research, particularly longitudinal studies, would be beneficial to fully understand the long-term effects of rewarding students for good grades.